Chris Davie for Metro.co.uk Monday 20 Feb 2017 6:59 pm Theo Walcott starts in attack for Arsenalâ€™s FA Cup clash vs Sutton United. (Getty Images) 
Theo Walcott starts in attack for Arsenalâ€™s FA Cup clash with Sutton United. 
Arsene Wenger has made seven changes following the 5-1 defeat to Bayern Munich in the Champions League last week, with David Ospina, Shkodran Mustafi, Granit Xhaka and Alex Iwobi the only players to keep their place. 
In defence, Gabriel replaces Hector Bellerin, Rob Holding partners Mustafi at centre-back, while Nacho Monreal is preferred to Kieran Gibbs at left-back.
